# Plan: Add `image-text-to-text` Pipeline to Transformers.js

## Context

The Transformers.js library already defines `AutoModelForImageTextToText` in `src/models.js`, which maps to 11 vision-language model classes (Florence-2, Llava, SmolVLM, PaliGemma, Qwen2-VL, etc.). However, there is no corresponding `ImageTextToTextPipeline` class or `"image-text-to-text"` task registered in `src/pipelines.js`. This plan adds that pipeline so users can easily run multimodal (image + text prompt → text) inference using the same `pipeline()` factory used for all other tasks.

**Primary reference pipelines:**
- `ImageToTextPipeline` (lines 1943–2005) — image → text with `generate()` + `batch_decode()`
- `DocumentQuestionAnsweringPipeline` (lines 2704–2779) — image + text → text, uses both processor and tokenizer

---

## Critical File

**`src/pipelines.js`** — the only file to be modified.

---

## Step-by-Step Implementation

### Step 1 — Add Import for `AutoModelForImageTextToText` (line ~40–44)

In the `import { ... } from './models.js'` block (lines 20–45), add `AutoModelForImageTextToText` after `AutoModelForDocumentQuestionAnswering`:

```js
import {
    AutoModel,
    AutoModelForSequenceClassification,
    // ... (all existing entries unchanged) ...
    AutoModelForDocumentQuestionAnswering,
    AutoModelForImageTextToText,      // ← ADD THIS LINE
    AutoModelForImageToImage,
    // ...
} from './models.js';
```

---

### Step 2 — Add JSDoc Typedefs, Callback, and Class (after line 2005)

Insert immediately after the closing `}` of `ImageToTextPipeline` (line 2005), before the `ImageClassificationPipeline` JSDoc block:

```js
/**
 * @typedef {Object} ImageTextToTextSingle
 * @property {string} generated_text The generated text.
 * @typedef {ImageTextToTextSingle[]} ImageTextToTextOutput
 *
 * @callback ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback Processes an image and a text prompt to generate text.
 * @param {ImageInput} image The input image.
 * @param {string} text The text prompt describing the task (e.g., "Describe this image in detail").
 * @param {Partial<import('./generation/configuration_utils.js').GenerationConfig>} [options] Additional keyword arguments to pass along to the generate method of the model.
 * @returns {Promise<ImageTextToTextOutput>} An array of objects containing the generated text(s).
 *
 * @typedef {TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs & ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback & Disposable} ImageTextToTextPipelineType
 */

/**
 * Image text-to-text pipeline using `AutoModelForImageTextToText`. This pipeline accepts an image
 * and a text prompt and generates text based on both inputs.
 *
 * **Example:** Generate a description for an image w/ `onnx-community/Florence-2-base-ft`.
 * ```javascript
 * const pipe = await pipeline('image-text-to-text', 'onnx-community/Florence-2-base-ft');
 * const url = 'https://huggingface.co/datasets/Xenova/transformers.js-docs/resolve/main/cats.jpg';
 * const output = await pipe(url, 'Describe this image in detail');
 * // [{ generated_text: 'Two cats are resting on a couch.' }]
 * ```
 */
export class ImageTextToTextPipeline extends (/** @type {new (options: TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs) => ImageTextToTextPipelineType} */ (Pipeline)) {

    /**
     * Create a new ImageTextToTextPipeline.
     * @param {TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs} options An object used to instantiate the pipeline.
     */
    constructor(options) {
        super(options);
    }

    /** @type {ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback} */
    async _call(image, text, generate_kwargs = {}) {

        // NOTE: For now, we only support a batch size of 1

        // Preprocess image
        const preparedImage = (await prepareImages(image))[0];
        const { pixel_values } = await this.processor(preparedImage);

        // Tokenize text prompt
        const { input_ids } = this.tokenizer(text, {
            padding: true,
            truncation: true,
        });

        // Run model
        const output = await this.model.generate({
            inputs: input_ids,
            pixel_values,
            ...generate_kwargs,
        });

        // Decode output
        const decoded = this.tokenizer.batch_decode(/** @type {Tensor} */(output), {
            skip_special_tokens: true,
        }).map(x => ({ generated_text: x.trim() }));

        return decoded;
    }
}
```

**Design notes:**
- Follows `DocumentQuestionAnsweringPipeline` for batch-size-1 pattern (single image).
